ratings.comment: Loved the class, learned so much about the history of the internet through engaging  lectures and interesting readings. There are a set amount of pop quizzes throughout the semester, so be sure to do the readings.

Sarah is a super fun professor. Her lectures are engaging, and she makes sure the content is clear to understand from her students' perspective. CA346 was super interesting, and Sarah organizing the semester in a way that makes sense. There are 6 pop quizzes, with one getting dropped, so make sure to read! Great class, and would take again.

CA346 was a great class and I believe that is greatly due to Sarah. She made lectures relevant and exciting which made me not dread going to lecture. I was also lucky enough to have her for discussion and she took it upon herself to learn each students name and get to know us which I thought was really cool. She gives good feedback but grades tough

Sarah was a great instructor. She genuinely cared about the subject and every lecture was extremely thought out and organized. She made lectures interesting with videos, memes, and songs. You'll have to do the readings, but they aren't tough. Would love to take another course taught by her! Would recommend this course to anyone!
